race.comment: ZOURAIN (4) found the 1200m too sharp first up at Sale but boxed on well enough for a midfield finish, beaten three lengths. His form over a bit further last time in reads very well for this and with even luck from the wide gate he should go close. SHAALUTE (1) is flying, winning four of his past five starts. He came from a long way back to score at Mornington over 1200m last time and should be even better suited to 1400m, although another wide draw likely sees him a long way back. HOLA AMIGOS (5) was just fair fresh but this is easier and 1400m is far more suitable. LETHAL THOUGHTS (2) was better last time and his best form would go close.
